    {
      "gridPos": { "h": 3, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 0 },
      "id": 10,
      "options": {
        "code": { "language": "plaintext", "showLineNumbers": false, "showMiniMap": false },
        "content": "## Sliding Window mode — Timeline Controller\n\nThe Timeline Controller below writes `timeFrom` / `timeTo` / `step` template variables on every tick (Unix milliseconds for the bounds). The text panel re-renders each tick with the current bounds rendered as ISO datetimes; the CPU stat re-aggregates over the chosen step. The CPU chart at the bottom uses a Mixed datasource — Prometheus for the metric, and Grafana's built-in TestData for a small CSV that draws the **window overlay** as a translucent band. Press Play and watch the band slide across the chart.\n\nKeyboard: **K** play/pause, **J** play backward, **`,`** / **`.`** step, **Home** / **End** jump to edges. Click anywhere on the Timeline Controller panel first so the keys are armed.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "12.4.0",
      "title": "",
      "type": "text"
    },
    {
      "gridPos": { "h": 4, "w": 16, "x": 0, "y": 3 },
      "id": 1,
      "options": {
        "mode": "sliding",
        "sliding": {
          "horizontalAlignment": "center",
          "initialPosition": "start",
          "showProgressTrack": true,
          "tickIntervalMs": 1000,
          "timeStep": "5m",
          "variableFrom": "timeFrom",
          "variableTo": "timeTo",
          "variableStep": "step",
          "verticalAlignment": "middle"
        }
      },
      "pluginVersion": "1.0.0",
      "title": "",
      "type": "evaldasguogis-timelinecontroller-panel"
    },
    {
      "gridPos": { "h": 4, "w": 8, "x": 16, "y": 3 },
      "id": 11,
      "options": {
        "code": { "language": "plaintext", "showLineNumbers": false, "showMiniMap": false },
        "content": "### Current window\n\n**From:** `${timeFrom:date:iso}`  \n**To:**  `${timeTo:date:iso}`  \n**Step:** `${step}`\n\n_Updated each tick by the Timeline Controller. Variable values are Unix milliseconds; the `:date:iso` formatter renders them as ISO datetimes._",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "12.4.0",
      "title": "",
      "type": "text"
    },
    {
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prom-demo" },
      "description": "Average CPU utilization evaluated **at the playhead** — `rate(node_cpu_seconds_total{mode=\"idle\"}[$step] @ ${timeTo:date:seconds})`. The `:date:seconds` formatter converts the ms variable to a Unix-seconds literal that PromQL's `@` modifier accepts. The number changes each tick as the window slides.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": { "mode": "thresholds" },
          "mappings": [],
          "max": 100,
          "min": 0,
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              { "color": "green", "value": 0 },
              { "color": "orange", "value": 60 },
              { "color": "red", "value": 80 }
            ]
          },
          "unit": "percent"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "gridPos": { "h": 4, "w": 8, "x": 0, "y": 7 },
      "id": 2,
      "options": {
        "colorMode": "background",
        "graphMode": "none",
        "justifyMode": "center",
        "orientation": "auto",
        "reduceOptions": { "calcs": ["lastNotNull"], "fields": "", "values": false },
        "showPercentChange": false,
        "textMode": "auto"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "12.4.0",
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prom-demo" },
          "expr": "100 - (avg(rate(node_cpu_seconds_total{mode=\"idle\"}[$step] @ ${timeTo:date:seconds})) * 100)",
          "instant": true,
          "legendFormat": "CPU",
          "range": false,
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "title": "CPU at playhead",
      "type": "stat"
    },
    {
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prom-demo" },
      "datasource": { "type": "datasource", "uid": "-- Mixed --" },
      "description": "CPU rate across the full dashboard range with a translucent band marking the current window. The band query is a TestData CSV with two rows at `${timeFrom}` and `${timeTo}` — datasource-neutral because TestData ships with every Grafana install. The metric query stays Prometheus-only and would change per dataset.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
